  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "基本歸因謬誤 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-fundamental-attribution-error",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / attribution / situation / judgment</p>\n    <h1>基本歸因謬誤</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Fundamental Attribution Error</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">看到別人做出糟糕選擇時，我們很容易先想到他這個人怎麼樣，卻低估情境、資訊與制度摩擦其實對行為有多大塑形力。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『這人就是不行』和『這個情境本來就很容易把人推錯』拆開，因為許多協作衝突都在高估人格、低估系統。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>社會認知 / 歸因偏差</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Overweighting character and underweighting situation when judging others</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>人格推論、情境因素、資訊可見性、制度摩擦</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在 review、incident 與跨團隊摩擦裡更平衡地看待人與情境的作用</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>人格</span>\n      <span>情境</span>\n      <span>失衡</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>別人出錯時，我們太容易先看見他的缺點，而不是他所站的地形</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">基本歸因謬誤抓到的是一種很穩定的不對稱：看自己時強調情境，看別人時強調人格。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>把問題快速讀成人格缺陷很省力，但它會讓你跳過更能被修復的介面、資訊與制度原因。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先問他看見了什麼</strong>\n        <p>很多看似荒謬的行為，是在資訊不完整或心智模型錯位下很可預期的結果。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再問情境怎麼推</strong>\n        <p>流程設計、優先序壓力與獎懲結構都會塑造行為。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後才談人格模式</strong>\n        <p>若要上升到人格推論，至少要看到跨情境、重複且更穩定的證據。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一次你差點想直接給人貼標籤的失誤開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">基本歸因謬誤在衝突、事故與跨部門合作裡特別容易發作。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>對方把需求做錯，你第一反應是『他很不用心』；後來才發現規格版本混亂、命名誤導且 review 邊界不清。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>人格解釋看起來最完整，但往往也最容易讓真正可修的機制被跳過。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">看到他人失誤</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">先用人格故事解釋</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">情境與制度因素被壓低</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>基本歸因謬誤最值得警覺的地方，是它會把系統問題偽裝成個人問題。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看歸因失衡的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">不是說人格永遠不重要，而是說它通常不該成為第一個、也是唯一一個解釋。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>資訊落差</strong>\n        <p>對方當時拿到的資料、限制與時序，和你現在看到的一樣嗎？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>制度摩擦</strong>\n        <p>流程是否本來就容易讓人遺漏、誤解或被迫取捨？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>重複模式</strong>\n        <p>這是單次情境失手，還是跨場景都反覆出現的穩定行為？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>角色視角</strong>\n        <p>換成你站在同樣資訊與壓力下，真的一定不會犯同樣錯嗎？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>現象</th>\n            <th>人格歸因版本</th>\n            <th>情境歸因版本</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>回覆很慢</td>\n            <td>他不負責</td>\n            <td>可能卡在權限、資訊來源或優先級衝突</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>把需求做反</td>\n            <td>他不細心</td>\n            <td>可能規格含混、術語誤導或版本不同</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>會議態度差</td>\n            <td>他難合作</td>\n            <td>可能長期壓力、責任不清或溝通結構已失衡</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼人格解釋這麼有吸引力</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為人格敘事簡單、完整、情緒上也更有結尾感。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>人格故事更省力</strong>\n        <p>用性格解釋別人的行為，比重建情境與制度更快。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>情境常不可見</strong>\n        <p>外部觀察者看不到對方當下的限制與資訊缺口。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>責怪能快速收束情緒</strong>\n        <p>一旦有了『就是他』的故事，混亂會立刻變得有出口。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">這個偏誤不是叫你永遠替人找藉口，而是提醒你別太快把診斷偷換成宣判。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把情境視角帶回事故與協作</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與跨團隊合作來說，能不能抵抗基本歸因謬誤，直接影響你修的是人還是系統。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Incident review</strong>\n        <p>若每次都先找誰出包，流程與介面缺陷就會持續藏在同樣位置。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Code review</strong>\n        <p>看到奇怪寫法時，先問是設計限制、歷史相容還是知識落差，比直接貼能力標籤更有用。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>跨部門協作</strong>\n        <p>把他人摩擦先讀成態度問題，常會讓原本能修的對齊機制變成長期敵意。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>每次想給人貼標籤前，先列出三個足以產生同樣行為的情境因素。</li>\n      <li>如果最後真的要談責任，也請先把系統摩擦寫清楚，避免下次重演。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">基本歸因謬誤不是說人格不重要，而是說我們通常太早太重地把它拿來解釋他人。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>所以都是系統的錯</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。只是責任判斷不該跳過情境分析。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這和 Hanlon&#x27;s Razor 完全一樣</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>兩者相近，但這個偏誤更聚焦於高估人格、低估情境的心理機制。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只在衝突時才有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>日常回覆、評論與管理判斷也都很常見。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我現在看到的是這個人，還是這個人加上他所處的地形</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在評價他人前。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果把同樣情境換到另一個人身上，我還會這麼確定這是人格問題嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你看見情境力量被低估的程度。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>對方當時有哪些限制是我現在站在事後看不見的</strong>\n        <p>很多錯誤解釋會在這一步被鬆開。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 attribution theory、Hanlon&#x27;s Razor 與 blame culture。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 fundamental attribution error 為主，再把概念帶回事故回顧、review 與跨團隊協作。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Fundamental attribution error 條目整理了人如何在看他人時高估人格、低估情境。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fundamental_attribution_error\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Fundamental Attribution Error</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>理論背景</strong>\n        <p>Attribution 條目可作為更一般背景，理解人如何解釋行為原因。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attribution_(psychology)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Attribution</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰偏誤</strong>\n        <p>Actor-observer asymmetry 條目可作為對照，看人如何對自己與他人採用不同解釋。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Actor%E2%80%93observer_asymmetry\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Actor-Observer Asymmetry</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個最近讓你不爽的協作事件，先把人格形容詞全部拿掉，再重寫一次原因假說。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
